Sed is a Stream EDitor, used as a filter in pipelines. It's NOT primarily useful to edit files in a script (use ed(1) or vi(1) instead). See http://www.student.northpark.edu/pemente/sed/sed1line.txt and http://sed.sourceforge.net/sedfaq.html and http://wooledge.org/mywiki/BashPitfalls and http://www.grymoire.com/Unix/Sed.html
